<Layout title="Ryan Prescott - Developer, Musician & Creator">
  <div class="container">
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="hero">
      <img src="/ryan-p-headshot.jpeg" alt="Ryan Prescott" class="headshot" />
      <h1 class="hero-name">ryan prescott<span class="hero-cursor"></span></h1>
      <p class="tagline">writing code & songs, usually at the same time</p>
      <p class="intro">
        Developer from Eastern Maine with 8+ years exp. building things that actually work.
        I spend most of my time architecting complex systems, but I'm just as likely to be
        writing a song, messing with my homelab, or troubleshooting whatever my friends broke this time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- About / Philosophy -->
    <section id="about">
      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Code is just the output. What actually matters 
        is understanding the problem, aligning the 
        team, and shipping something that moves the
        needle. LLMs forced me to realize that when
        anyone can generate code, the best engineers
        are the ones who can see the big picture.
      </p>
      <p>
        These days my focus is on systems, not syntax.
        How do we structure the work? Who owns
        what? What's the fastest path to learning if
        we're wrong? Everyone can write code now.
        Execution is what separates people.
      </p>
      <p>
        I still enjoy the craft, though. And I'll
        always have a soft spot for rescuing legacy
        systems from the brink.
      </p>
    </section>

